Elastic net regression was chosen for the predictive algorithm because it has two regularisation terms that prevent overfitting.
 The regularisation terms are tuned by varying the two hyperparameters (alpha and lambda) to determine each regularisation term's optimal weight, resulting in cross-validated accuracy

